-- Global Refining Margin Rose to $5.49 a Barrel in Second Quarter, BP Says
-- Rachel Graham
-- 2010-07-05T15:14:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/global-refining-margin-rose-to-5-49-a-barrel-in-second-quarter-bp-says.html

          
          
             Global refining margins, or the
profit from turning crude oil into fuels, rose to $5.49 a barrel
in the second quarter compared with $4.98 a year ago, according
to data published by BP Plc today.  
